  'Slavic':              '#9b2640',  // Rushnyk embroidery red — the deep ritual-red-on-white of Slavic embroidered ceremonial textiles; the rushnyk (East Slavic) and ručnik (South Slavic) are foundational Slavic ritual-textiles used in weddings, funerals, and harvest-festivals; the embroidered red preserves continuous Slavic cultural-identity from polytheistic agricultural-ritual tradition through the modern era; chemically based on madder-root and Balkan-cochineal natural dyes
  'Arabian': '#d4b87a',  // Frankincense pale-gold — the warm-pale-yellow of frankincense (luban) resin, the foundational Arabian luxury-trade commodity (cultivated principally in Dhofar, Hadramawt, and the broader South Arabian Boswellia-tree zones) that anchored the Arabian-Mediterranean-South-Asian Incense Route from at least the 1st millennium BCE; iconographically central to the South Arabian Sabaean-Himyarite-Qatabānian temple-economies and to the Nabataean Petra-as-Incense-trade-hub
