  'Finnish':             '#3d6655',  // Karelian forest-green — the dark-teal-green of the Finnish-Karelian boreal-forest-and-lakeland landscape that anchored the Kalevala oral-tradition setting; the Karelian Isthmus and broader Finnish-Karelian cultural region (where Elias Lönnrot collected the runo-singing material 1828-1849) is geographically dominated by the boreal-pine-spruce-birch forest interspersed with lakes, encoding the foundational Finnish-cultural landscape
