  'Maya':                '#3aa6c8',  // Maya Blue (azul maya) — the iconic Mesoamerican pigment of indigo + palygorskite clay; the saturated turquoise-azure of the Bonampak murals (c. 800 CE), the Cacaxtla battle frescoes, the Chichen Itza Sacred Cenote sacrificial offerings; chemically and optically distinct from Old World blues; the only ancient pigment to remain stable in tropical humidity for over a millennium
  'Mixtec':              '#2c8995',  // Yacaxihuitl turquoise mosaic — the Mixtec polychrome lapidary signature; the turquoise of the nose-ornament received by Lord 8 Deer Jaguar Claw from Lord 4 Jaguar of Cholula in 1097 CE; the British Museum Mictlantecuhtli mosaic mask, the Yanhuitlán turquoise mosaic shield, and the Codex Zouche-Nuttall turquoise-jewelry depictions; distinct from Maya Blue by being a desaturated mineral-mosaic turquoise rather than a vegetal-clay blue
  'Apapocúva-Guaraní':   '#c0461e',  // Annatto / urucum
