  'Macuxi':              '#a55a3a',  // Roraima tepui sandstone-coral — the warm orange-red of the Roraima-formation Precambrian sandstone that geologically anchors Macuxi territory in the tri-border region (Brazil/Venezuela/Guyana); the tepui-cliff face of Mount Roraima is the foundational landscape-cosmological feature of Macuxi origin-narrative tradition documented by Im Thurn (1883) and Koch-Grünberg (1924)
