          etymology: 'Pakhangba/Pakhangpa: "the one who knows his father" — pa (father) + khangba (knower-of). The honorific name marks the divine-paternity-recognition motif at the heart of the divine-paternity tradition. Thangwai = the prefix-name acquired by his foster-father Khongding Ahanba ("the elder") via the Moirang convention of addressing parents using their first child\'s name as a prefix.',
