        etymology: 'Finnish Louhi; etymology contested. Possible derivation from Old Finnish louhia "to hew, to break apart," matching the destructive-sorceress domain. The Pohjolan emäntä title (pohjola "the North-Land" + emäntä "mistress, hostess, lady-of-the-house") preserves her foundational-realm-affiliation.',
