      lifecycle: [
        { typeStatus: 'mortal', startEvent: 'kingship-of-Dyfed-and-Annwn-year-exchange-with-Arawn', era: 'mabinogion-mythological', eraOrdering: 0, sources: [{ kind: 'primary', reference: 'Mabinogion First Branch' }], notes: 'Prince of Dyfed. Earned the epithet Pen Annwn ("Head of Annwn") through a year-and-a-day shape-exchange with Arawn, king of Annwn (the Welsh Otherworld), during which Pwyll ruled Annwn in Arawn\'s shape and defeated Arawn\'s rival Hafgan in single combat — establishing Pwyll\'s otherworldly associations that pre-date his Rhiannon-marriage.' },
        { typeStatus: 'mortal', startEvent: 'meeting-Rhiannon-at-Gorsedd-Arberth', era: 'mabinogion-mythological', eraOrdering: 1, sources: [{ kind: 'primary', reference: 'Mabinogion First Branch' }], notes: 'At the ancestral mound of Gorsedd Arberth, saw Rhiannon riding her uncatchable white horse; called out to her; she stopped. Marriage arranged at her father Hyfaidd Hen\'s court, with the bag-trick deployed against the rival Gwawl.' },
        { typeStatus: 'mortal', startEvent: 'Pryderi-birth-and-Rhiannon-trial', era: 'mabinogion-mythological', eraOrdering: 2, sources: [{ kind: 'primary', reference: 'Mabinogion First Branch' }], notes: 'Three years into the marriage, Rhiannon bore a son. The newborn was abducted by a black-clawed apparition while her nursemaids slept; they smeared Rhiannon with puppy-blood and accused her of infanticide. Pwyll inflicted on her the seven-year horse-block punishment at the gate of Arberth.' },
        { typeStatus: 'mortal', startEvent: 'restoration-of-Pryderi-and-naming', era: 'mabinogion-mythological', eraOrdering: 3, sources: [{ kind: 'primary', reference: 'Mabinogion First Branch' }], notes: 'Pryderi restored to the court by Teyrnon Twrf Liant of Gwent Ys-coed, who had found and raised the boy after rescuing him from the same black-clawed apparition that nightly stole Teyrnon\'s mare-foals. Recognized by his resemblance to Pwyll. Rhiannon vindicated; named the boy "Pryderi" ("anxiety, care") because her grief and anxiety were now ended.' },
      ],
