      notes: 'Foundational creator-figure of the Diné Bahaneʼ cosmology; mother of the Hero Twins. Discovered as a cosmic-egg by Áłtsé Hastiin (First Man) on Gobernador Knob (Ch\'óol\'į́\'í), raised to maturity in twelve days through the canonical Diné kinaaldá (puberty-and-becoming) ceremony — the foundational Diné female-initiation rite continuously practiced through the present. Conceived the Hero Twins through union with Jóhonaaʼéí (the Sun, father of Monster Slayer) and a waterfall (father of Born for Water). The "changing" in her name refers to cyclical-renewal across the seasons (young in spring, mature in summer, aged in winter, reborn in spring) — the canonical Diné female-creator cyclic-renewal complex. The four-directions coloration of her cyclical-renewal (east-white-spring, south-blue-summer, west-yellow-autumn, north-black-winter) maps onto the Diné cardinal-directions cosmological framework. The kinaaldá ceremony continues as the foundational Diné female-initiation rite, performed for Diné girls at first menstruation across the contemporary Diné Nation. registered with parentIds=[] per pantheon-deity convention; the cosmic-egg-on-Gobernador-Knob origin is treated as primordial-creator emergence rather than parent-attributed birth.',
