    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    //  IROQUOIS (Haudenosaunee) — Sky Woman cosmogony + Confederacy founder
    //  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    //  The Haudenosaunee (Iroquois Confederacy: Mohawk, Oneida, Onondaga,
    //  Cayuga, Seneca, with Tuscarora joining as the sixth nation post-
    //  c.1722) cosmological-religious tradition centers on the Sky Woman
    //  cosmogony — the primordial mother who fell from the Sky Country
    //  through a hole in the firmament, was caught by water-birds and laid
    //  on the back of the Great Turtle, who then accumulated mud brought
    //  up from the ocean-floor by the muskrat to form the foundational
    //  earth-on-Turtle\'s-back (the Iroquois cosmological designation
    //  "Turtle Island" for North America).
    //
    //  The historical-legendary Hayowentha (Hiawatha) co-founded the
    //  Haudenosaunee Confederacy with Deganawida (the Great Peacemaker)
    //  by bringing the Great Law of Peace (Kaianerékowa) to the original
    //  five Iroquois nations, ending the inter-tribal warfare and
    //  establishing the foundational political-confederation that
    //  influenced (per the Iroquois-influence-on-the-US-Constitution
    //  thesis, which is contested but widely-discussed) the structure of
    //  modern federalism.
    //
    //  Sources: Arthur C. Parker, The Constitution of the Five Nations
