        etymology: 'K\'iche\' Xmukane; archaic theonym, opaque to standard K\'iche\'. The x- prefix marks feminine/diminutive; -mukan- has been related by Tedlock (1996) to the verb root for "to bury" or "to hide" (compare K\'iche\' muqu, "to bury") with the agentive -e suffix, possibly "she-who-buries/hides" in the day-keeping divinatory sense (the seed-cast that conceals before revealing). Christenson treats both names as opaque archaic.',
