        etymology: 'Iya Nacuaa ("Lord 8 Deer," day-name combining numerical 8 with day-sign Cuaa "Deer") + Teyusi Ñaña (personal-epithet "Jaguar Claw"; teyusi "claw" + ñaña "jaguar"). The full name follows the standard Mixtec onomastic pattern: Iya + calendar-day-name + personal-epithet.',
