        etymology: 'Wiraqocha (the creator-deity\'s name; etymology contested — Garcilaso glosses as wira "fat, foam" + qocha "lake/sea," "foam-of-the-sea"; modern Quechua linguists (Mannheim) propose alternative etymologies including a possible Aymara loan) + Inka (imperial-state title). The compound functions as "Inka of Viracocha" or "Viracocha-named Inka," asserting divine-vision-derived royal legitimacy.',
