    // PHASE 9 — LATE BRONZE AGE FIGURES (alive at c. 1172 BCE)
    //
    // Adds figures across Egyptian (19th-20th Dynasty), Hittite, Mesopotamian,
    // and Levantine traditions who were demonstrably active during the Bronze
    // Age Collapse window. All entries pass the strict no-nymph-parent rule
    // because their typing paths are: Egyptian doctrinal Birth Cycle (Amun +
    // mortal queen → demigod), Hittite scion-tier through deified-king-
    // ancestor lineage, or mortal-class for figures with two attested
    // historical mortal parents.
    //
    // The Birth Cycle convention used here matches the existing Egyptian
    // pharaohs in the registry: Hatshepsut, Amenhotep III, Ramesses II all
    // typed as demigods of Amun via their respective Great Royal Wife
    // mothers. Maintained consistently for Seti II, Tausret, Ramesses III.
    // Setnakhte (founder of the 20th Dynasty) is a special case — his
    // origins are unknown and the Birth Cycle does not seem to have been
    // doctrinally applied to him in surviving inscriptions; encoded as
    // mortal-class. Tiy-Merenese (mother of Ramesses III, mortal queen)
    // is also added as the maternal anchor for Birth Cycle attribution.
    // ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    // ─── Seti II (Egyptian, 19th Dynasty, r. 1203-1197 BCE) ───────────────
