        etymology: 'Twi-Akan Opoku (a personal-name; possibly opoku "tortoise" in some readings, indicating a clan-totem) + Ware (Twi ware "to marry"; possibly "much-married" or a clan-name). The Katakyie ("Brave") praise-name was earned through the imperial conquest reign.',
