        transliterations: { 'welsh': 'Lleu Llaw Gyffes', etymology: 'Welsh Lleu from Proto-Celtic *Lugus — cognate with Irish Lugh and Continental-Celtic Lugus (the Lugdunum / Lyon eponymous deity); the canonical-Celtic *Lugus pan-Celtic deity-figure (skilled craftsman-warrior-king) is the underlying figure of all three regional manifestations. The Welsh epithet Llaw Gyffes ("Skillful Hand") was given by Arianrhod when she saw him kill a wren with a single stone-throw — the canonical-Welsh circumvention-of-the-no-name-tynged trick at the cobbler\'s shop. The Welsh Lleu is the Mabinogion-Fourth-Branch reflex of the canonical pan-Celtic *Lugus.' },
