        etymology: 'Welsh Branwen; bran "raven, crow" + (g)wen "fair, white, blessed." Literally "Fair Raven" or "White Raven." The brân-element pairs with her brother Bendigeidfran ("Blessed Raven") — the sibling-pair share the foundational raven-onomastic root.',
