        etymology: 'Welsh Math; etymology contested. Possibly cognate with Old Irish math "good, fortunate" or with the broader Indo-European *meh₂- "great." The patronymic fab Mathonwy preserves an earlier-generation name (Mathonwy) attested only through this filiation.',
