  // 568 CE) is the cosmogonic anchor period that the royal genealogies
  // structurally point to. Viking Age (793 CE Lindisfarne raid through 1066
  // CE Stamford Bridge) is the cult-active period. Christianization (10th-
  // 12th c. CE region by region — Iceland 1000 CE Alþingi conversion, Norway
  // 1015-1030 Olav, Denmark 965 Harald Bluetooth at Jelling, Sweden 11th-12th
  // c.). Medieval-saga (13th c. — Snorri's Prose Edda c. 1220, Heimskringla
  // c. 1230, the Codex Regius of the Poetic Edda c. 1270) is the textual-
  // recording period, separated from the cult by 200+ years of Christianization.
